RECOMMENDED VAxAI ENTRY: AI training & adoption (primary)

WHY ADMIN / AI PRESSURE IS HIGH:
Client onboarding (AML/KYC), bookkeeping data entry, VAT/CT return prep, payroll runs, year-end workpapers, client chase for records, practice management time recording, and MTD compliance admin.

UK AI ADOPTION (use in conversation):
Barclays Business Prosperity Index (Aug 2025): 89% of UK businesses plan AI use within two years; SMEs (10–49 staff) averaged £125k AI investment vs £400k for 250+ employee firms. Lloyds Business Barometer (Mar 2026): 66% have invested in AI, mostly under £25k—39% cite AI/digital skills shortage. ICAEW surveys show practices experimenting with AI for bookkeeping categorisation but lack firm-wide training.

WHERE VA ALONE IS NOT THE RIGHT LEAD:
VA is not the lead when receipt/invoice extraction or MTD filing prep can be automated—train staff on AI-assisted review.

SUGGESTED CALL HOOKS / DISCOVERY QUESTIONS:
• AI-assisted bookkeeping review
• Automate client document chase
• Copilot training for management letters

DISCOVERY PROMPTS FOR THIS CALL:
• How much time does the team spend on the highest-volume admin tasks in accountancy practices (sme, not big 4)?
• Have they piloted AI tools internally, or only client-facing tech?
• Who owns operations/process improvement — and is AI training on anyone''s KPIs?
• What would ''win'' look like in 90 days: hours saved, fewer errors, or staff confident using AI?

